---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import '../../styles/scenario.css';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Base title="Block Party Trade-Up | Copilot Studio technical guide">
  <article class="scenario">
    <div class="container">
      <a href={base} class="back">&larr; All scenarios</a>

      <header class="scenario__header">
        <h1>Block Party Trade-Up</h1>
        <p class="scenario__lead">
          It's the weekend of a gaming-league block party, and one of the hosts has a problem:
          the console he bought just ten days ago has given out on him, right when he needs it
          most. He comes into the store with his receipt, unsure whether he wants a replacement,
          a refund, or an upgrade, and while he's there he'd like to cancel his BlastPass too.
          The associate turns to the <strong>Store Associate Assistant</strong> to untangle all
          of it in a single conversation.
        </p>
        <div class="scenario__agent" style="--accent: var(--c-purple);">
          <span class="scenario__agent-icon"><svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="10" rx="2"/><circle cx="12" cy="5" r="2"/><path d="M12 7v4"/><line x1="8" y1="16" x2="8.01" y2="16"/><line x1="16" y1="16" x2="16.01" y2="16"/></svg></span>
          <span class="scenario__agent-text">
            <span class="scenario__agent-label">Test this scenario with</span>
            <span class="scenario__agent-name">Store Associate Assistant</span>
          </span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="convo">
        <h2>The conversation</h2>

        <ol class="timeline">
          <li class="tl-user">
            <div class="tl-marker">1</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Associate</div>
              <div class="try-prompt">
                <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">Customer's running a gaming-league block party this weekend and his main console just gave out about 10 days after he bought it, and he's got the receipt. He wants a replacement if one's in stock, otherwise a refund, and while he's here he wants to cancel his BlastPass, member ID MEGA-BLAST-1024. Walk me through all of it.</blockquote>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="tl-agent">
            <div class="tl-marker">&#9670;</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Agent &rarr; connected agents &rarr; Associate</div>
              <div class="tl-steps">
                <p>The orchestrator fans out and front-loads the whole picture in a single pass, rather than asking one question at a time.</p>
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">get_membership</span> reads MEGA-BLAST-1024 (Plus Extra, 8 months unused, $10 fee)</div>
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Store Policy Agent &middot; search_policy</span> "defective console warranty vs accidental damage" &rarr; returns a <em>question</em>, not a ruling (its rule is to establish the defect cause first)</div>
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Order Management MCP &middot; search_orders</span> finds nothing under the member ID, so it retries <strong>by customer name</strong> (Jordan Pixel) and gets a hit</div>
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">get_order</span> &rarr; ORD-10502: BlastBox Omega, $399.99 on Visa ending 1024, inside the 30-day defective window</div>
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Inventory &amp; Fulfillment Agent &middot; Warehouse MCP</span> check_stock (base = 0 local), get_restock_date (~4 days), find_alternatives (MEGA Edition, $499.99, 5 in stock)</div>
                <div class="tl-skill"><span class="tl-skill-name">prorated-refund-calculator</span> runs Python &rarr; $129.99 ÷ 12 × 8 &minus; $10 = <strong>$76.66</strong></div>
                <p>It lays out the console options &mdash; <strong>wait ~4 days</strong> for the base restock, <strong>upgrade to the MEGA Edition</strong> now (the $76.66 BlastPass refund covers most of the $100 gap &rarr; <strong>$23.34</strong> net), or a <strong>full refund</strong> &mdash; plus the BlastPass cancellation breakdown, then asks the one thing that gates it all: <strong>"manufacturing defect, or physical / liquid damage?"</strong></p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="tl-user">
            <div class="tl-marker">2</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Associate</div>
              <div class="try-prompt">
                <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">Manufacturing fault, just won't power on, no physical or liquid damage.</blockquote>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="tl-agent">
            <div class="tl-marker">&#9670;</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Agent</div>
              <div class="tl-steps">
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Store Policy Agent</span> confirms defective within 30 days = free warranty swap, no restocking fee</div>
                <p>With the cause settled, the warranty-swap path locks in. Nothing new has to be looked up &mdash; orders, stock, and the $76.66 refund were already pulled in the first pass.</p>
                <p>"Confirmed: manufacturing defect inside 30 days &rarr; free warranty swap, no fee. The base console is out of stock, so it's: wait ~4 days for the restock, upgrade to the MEGA Edition today (his <strong>$76.66</strong> refund covers most of the $100 difference &rarr; <strong>$23.34</strong> net), or take a full refund. Which way is he leaning?"</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="tl-user">
            <div class="tl-marker">3</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Associate</div>
              <div class="try-prompt">
                <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">He's torn: he likes the MEGA Edition but isn't sure it's worth the extra hundred over just waiting four days for the base console. Give me something I can tell him.</blockquote>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="tl-agent">
            <div class="tl-marker">&#9670;</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Agent</div>
              <div class="tl-steps">
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Inventory &amp; Fulfillment Agent &middot; get_console_exclusives</span> "mega" &rarr; three MEGA-only AAA titles</div>
                <p><em>"The block party is this weekend. Waiting four days means he misses it. The deciding factor isn't the $100, it's the three games that physically won't run on the base console."</em></p>
                <p>"Two things settle it: <strong>timing</strong> (the MEGA Edition is the only option that gets him a working console before the weekend) and <strong>the games</strong>: <em>MEGA Lizards from Outer Space</em>, <em>Galactic Tax Evader VII</em>, and <em>Mecha-Granny: Knitpocalypse</em>, none of which load on the base console. Plus the $76.66 refund goes straight toward the upgrade, so the real gap is small."</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="tl-user">
            <div class="tl-marker">4</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Associate</div>
              <div class="try-prompt">
                <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">Do it: warranty-swap him into the MEGA Edition, cancel the BlastPass and apply the $76.66 as store credit toward the upgrade, and tell me what he owes. Also, after Triple BLAST Weekend, what are his BlastPoints worth? Then print me the slip as a PDF.</blockquote>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="tl-agent">
            <div class="tl-marker">&#9670;</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Agent &rarr; Associate</div>
              <div class="tl-steps">
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">check_game_compatibility</span> confirms all three titles require the MEGA Edition</div>
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Order Management MCP &middot; request_return</span> defective console, warranty exchange</div>
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Membership MCP &middot; cancel_membership</span> refund issued as store credit</div>
                <div class="tl-skill"><span class="tl-skill-name">points-reconciliation</span> runs Python &rarr; 4,200 + 18,000 earned &minus; 800 expired = <strong>21,400 pts &rarr; $105.00</strong></div>
                <div class="tl-skill"><span class="tl-skill-name">slip-pdf-generator</span> runs reportlab &rarr; settlement PDF</div>
                <div class="tl-file"><span class="ticon-cat"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/></svg></span><span class="ticon-bb">&#129534;</span> hands back <strong>blastbox_slip.pdf</strong></div>
                <p>"Defective console credited at $399.99, no fee. MEGA Edition $499.99 &rarr; upgrade difference $100.00. BlastPass cancelled &rarr; $76.66 store credit. <strong>Net due: $23.34.</strong> BlastPoints after the weekend: <strong>21,400</strong> (worth $105.00). He can redeem $23.34 to walk out owing $0."</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div class="result">
          <span class="result__icon"><span class="ticon-cat"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/></svg></span><span class="ticon-bb">&#129534;</span></span>
          <div>
            <div class="result__label">Settlement</div>
            <div class="result__value">$100 upgrade &minus; $76.66 credit = net due $23.34 &middot; 21,400 pts &rarr; $105 &middot; blastbox_slip.pdf</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>What was demonstrated</h2>
        <div class="value-grid">
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Two connected agents, two MCPs under them</h3>
            <p>Policy <em>rules</em> the defect, Inventory <em>stocks and upsells</em>, plus two parent MCPs. The orchestration genuinely fans out to specialists and comes back.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>The upsell closes a real decision</h3>
            <p>When the customer can't choose, <code>get_console_exclusives</code> hands the associate the exact words: three AAA titles that won't run on the base console, plus same-day availability for a weekend event.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Every number comes from Python</h3>
            <p>The agent passes MCP results to skills that compute the exact figures (prorated refund, loyalty points, settlement PDF). It never hand-rolls the arithmetic.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>What gets generated</h2>
        <p class="gen-note">
          The associate hands the customer a settlement slip, generated live by the
          <code>slip-pdf-generator</code> skill (reportlab) from the reconciled numbers.
          This is the actual PDF from a real run of the agent &mdash; download it to see
          exactly what a customer walks out with.
        </p>
        <div class="files">
          <a class="filecard filecard--download" href={`${base}files/blastbox_slip.pdf`} download>
            <span class="filecard__icon"><span class="ticon-cat"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/></svg></span><span class="ticon-bb">&#129534;</span></span>
            <div>
              <strong>blastbox_slip.pdf</strong>
              <span>reportlab &middot; settlement slip &middot; swap + cancellation + math</span>
            </div>
            <span class="filecard__dl">Download &darr;</span>
          </a>
        </div>
        <figure class="slip-preview">
          <a href={`${base}files/blastbox_slip.pdf`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <img
              src={`${base}img/blastbox_slip-preview.png`}
              alt="BlastBox Returns & Service settlement slip: warranty exchange of the defective console for the MEGA Edition, BlastPass cancellation refund applied as store credit, net due $23.34."
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </a>
        </figure>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
